<br>
What you have to remember is that being in a Guild is purely Voluntary. You have to be happy there. You also have to remember that this is actually a game and is intended to be fun...<br>
<br>
We are not a roleplaying guild and don't have any strict rules about who can play with what character, and from which guild etc etc... And I hope that we never get to that stage cos if we do, I for one will be on the first boat out of here...<br>
<br>
I do think that most people with alts in the guild have them here because it *is* such a friendly guild and people are generally happy here. But it doesn't mean that you have to have every alt in the guild, The only issue it might raise is if you attended a raid with an alt from another guild...but then raid points are given to a person and not their individual chars so actually that probably *wouldn't* cause an issue...!!<br>
<br>
I think that it would probably be good for you to have a character in another guild. it gives you a different perspective and different people to listen to/discuss things with/group with etc etc, and from what i can tell it will only enhance your gameplaying experience... Cornie has decided to spread her wings too and is in another guild (Norath's answer to Girl Power and Women's Lib lol)<br>
<br>
So, in short, it doesn't matter, at least to me and I'm sure it doesn't matter to anyone else either...we are a pretty laid back crew these days...so long as you keep in touch via the forum so you don't miss the *hot gossip* rofl<br>
<br>
